caption: Fresh sandwiches and lots of options, definitely worth the stop.
Great sandwiches so far, had the breakfast bagels. Nice little place, worth a visit. Called ahead and they were ready to pick up almost immediately. Delightful staff working :)

The bald guy making the sandwiches is a total Hot Head. I ordered 2 sandwiches and after waiting 20 minutes I simply asked for an ETA of when they would be done.  He became completely irate and said they were shorthand. Then he began yelling at me in some language at the top of his lungs.  I said forget about the order and walked out. He followed me to my car and continued to yell.  This guy is 1 sandwich short of a picnic.  I will never go there again.

caption: My go to sandwich spot nearby. Quick and fair price. Taste is great and exactly what you want. Always bring my friends here

Do not go here.  I went there today to get sandwiches to go. I asked to use the bathroom after I'd paid. They said it was only for staff. The cook threatened to hit me over the head with a stool, and sweared at me about how it was the mayors and governors fault, not his, that the restroom was closed. He stood in my face and threatened me again and forced me to leave.  I had already paid, and they did not give me the $26 of food. I ended up calling the police. They closed the store and wouldn't let anyone in when I tried to go back in.
This place has some of the best sandwiches around.  In fact, everything I've had here is excellent.

The paninis were alright but the coffee drinks were way too sweet. The food was expensive considering it was all just grocery store named brands. On top of this, there is a “5% discount” for using cash, which is a bit odd considering the current pandemic, but I assume they are just trying to offset transaction costs, so take that as you will.  The most alarming part though was a large sign regarding COVID-19 and prepared foods with circled text specifically about your stomach inactivating the virus. I noticed the cook did not wear a mask while preparing the food and the cashier was hardly wearing one properly, so I’m assuming they have had complaints prior to this. For the amount of signs inside regarding social distancing, I would assume they would take the appropriate precautions of their own.  Best to just stay away.
Was on my way to Jimmy Johns but went here instead. I made the right choice. The Southwest Diablo sandwich was awesome!
Tea was good but their service wasn't the most friendliest.

This place is great! I actually thought it was just a coffee shop at first but no, they have a full menu that they make fresh to order. Everything is ready very quickly and the prices are very reasonable. I’ve now tried many different lunch and breakfast sandwiches and have not been disappointed. I really enjoy that the breakfast sandwiches come on bagels that are perfectly toasted. They also have a really nice tea selection.  My go-to spot in Lakeview!

I absolutely love Aje Cafe, and you will too! I've gotten a different sandwich there every time. I have never been disappointed. The level of care and the quality of ingredients going into each sandwich is top-notch (even when you order for pick-up or delivery). Do yourself a favor and eat at Aje Cafe.

This coffee shop is owned by two beautiful people. I've never seen owners take such pride and care in their craft. From the sandwiches to coffee...this is THE SPOT. I will definitely be a regular to this cute cafe.
I just discovered this place that I've lived near for a couple years. Its such a hidden gem! Great coffee and I love the mozzarella caprese panini. Sooo good wish I could give more than 5 stars.
The staff is very welcoming and the bagel breakfast sandwiches are the best I’ve ever had.

Cool vibe inside the Aje Cafe, nice little homely place. They have breakfast, lunch, and cafe style options on the menu, good for meals, meetups and study sessions. I personally thought it was a little expensive for what it was, though the sandwhiches are a good size. I wouldn't say a must visit, but if you decide to go in, you won't regret it.
This place is amazing. The best breakfast sandwiches I’ve had in Chicago.

Good coffee, rude male server. Asked him for a spare cup, and he stated, they give two cups only when you pay for 2 coffees to manage the inventory. I have been to many local cafes over the years and this is the first time some one refused to give a spare paper cup to manage inventory. Won't go again due to him.
Great wraps!

Came in for a sandwich and drink with a friend but wasn’t allowed to stay unless he purchased something too? Love Aje Cafe for their coffee and sandwiches but seems like a silly requirement especially during a non busy time.

Went there for the tuna melt, bread and tuna was good but I believe they could add more stuff inside such as lettuce tomato cucumber. Had the berry smoothie that was good. Staff could smile a little bit more
Love their panini especially chicken panini. Good start for the day breakfast at this place! Service is great

They have a sign that says "good local business". That's wrong, it should be "great". Baked goods are great, sandwiches/wraps/salads are greater, and coffee/smoothies are the greatest. Best local cafe in Lakeview.
Nice , quite cafe. Friendly staff. Food is always fresh and tasteful. I'm never disappointed
Delicious, fresh food. Staff incredibly friendly. Support local!
Great relaxed cafe vibe, delicious drinks, and super tasty sandwiches! The sandwiches are loaded with toppings and filling, the coffee drinks are clearly made with care. We love coming to Aje's!
Beautiful downtown club on marbled rye toast, really enjoyable

A great neighborhood spot I found while walking by. Good food, good prices, good coffee, good service. Great discovery. Bonus points for the cute cat painting. :-)
Food is always great, coffee is always excellent, staff is always super nice. Do your self a favor and stop by.
Great sandwiches and coffee. And super nice staff. A good place to fuel up and also a nice spot to read the paper.

This cafe/sandwich shop is excellent! The sandwich I got was delicious and the potato salad on the side was to die for. The coffee was excellent and hot, and the atmosphere was lovely. They do have Wi-Fi, and I will likely be back on days I work out of the office.

This is my favorite cafe! The Dream smoothie with avacado is AMAZING. So creamy and flavorful. The prices are great too - you can get coffee and a breakfast sandwich for a great price. Space is also warm and inviting and I love the owners.
Great place, nice people, excellent food.
Great sandwiches and smoothies. Cozy place to get some work done.

Best Sandwhiches I've ever had! Joseph and Anna make every single sandwhich with their heart and soul and you can really see the passion that goes into Joseph's work as he crafts each like a masterpiece. The combination of flavors is intense. Warm bread and premium meats and cheeses, expertly brought together with organic greens and delicious sauces to make the perfect sandwhich. They also make amazing juices that make for a great pick me up or a delicious healthy desert. They also have free wifi and a cozy setting to eat, work, and just relax! Personally sandwhiches are my favorite food so I do not offer a review like this lightly, but I can honestly say that after 4 years of living here and searching, I am so thankful to have finally found my Chicago sandwhich shop. See you soon!

Worth going to for the turkey panini if you're in the area.  The turkey is sliced fresh so it's not dry.  Served with a side of potato salad which to me tasted homemade. Glad I went there the other day. Owners are nice too!
Great place for doing work or for meeting with friends. The service and food are always spectacular!
Yum!

Just wow!! Incredible food. Delicious.  But the cold brew coffee stopped me in my tracks. I brew my own and have for years. But this is special.  So many light notes! Raisins!? How did you get in there? Idk, but thank you!  Sweet fruity notes up front, and the chocolate finish, surprising and beautiful!  Just go already!!
Amazing sandwiches!

Sandwiches are really good.  Nice cozy place.
Been here years ago and again a few days ago. Still a really special sandwich shop.  There's a lot of love in everything they do.

I tried a lunch combo $6.99 Omg delicious.  soup/ 1/2 sandwich/ side salad deal. tomato soup was delicious and my salsalito turkey was amazingly put together. Best part was their fruit salad. Overall worth trying. Next time definitely try their breakfast combo .

Very nice cafe! I had their tomato soup and sweet matches tea. They were delicious! The staff were very nice and helpful. They are also reasonably priced.  I would definately come back here to try their sandwiches.
It's OK...
Quick, friendly service. Larger than expected menu. Most importantly, delicious food at a good price. Will definitely go back.
Great sandwiches
This is a really cozy breakfast/lunch place in Lakeview. Food is moderately priced and has been good whenever I've visited.

A comfy "mom & pop"  cafe with some great hand-built sandwiches and plenty of other selections to choose from. Plenty of seating and laptop friendly with in house wifi. Friendly staff. A personal favorite.

Great neighborhood breakfast spot. Their supreme veggie sandwich is my favorite, packed with cucumbers, lettuce, tomatoes, peppers and eggs. Highly recommend for easy breakfast in lake view!
Nice coffee and tea shop with good tasty lunches and available Wifi.

I have been here 3 times and everything has always been fantastic.  The veggies are so fresh, the sandwiches are perfect and the smoothies are full of real fruit and fresh oj. This is a perfect sanwich and coffee place!!

Delicious, carefully crafted sandwiches. Service is kind though on the slow side as each sandwich is so carefully prepared, so if you're in a huge hurry and that will stress, suggest coming a different time when you have 10 minutes to spare from ordering to receiving your food. Otherwise, Aje is a no brainer and one of my favorite sandwich shop in Chicago. Breakfast options look good too though have yet to try.
Sandwiches were good but cashier want that enthusiastic as if she would rather be doing something else
A really comfortable cafe with a nice vibe and good eats!
I had the classic smoothie and avocado BLT which was fantastic. A nice quiet place to get a bite to eat or just sit and get some work done, very cozy.
Great service and food!
My go-to place for coffee in Lakeview. It's never over-crowded, and it's a great place to get some work done or grab a bite for lunch with friends.

My absolute favorite place in the neighborhood! Great food and FANTASTIC staff that's there almost every day of the year! Always a good study spot, work spot, or just a great place to just grab some breakfast or lunch. Highly recommend to everyone and anyone. They do it right here!
Great wraps

I've been coming to Aje since 2013 and the food is consistently fresh and delicious. The owners are very conscientious about the quality of their products and I've never had a negative experience. This a preferred local lunch spot in East Lakeview.
Nice quaint cafe. Great place to take a laptop and spend a few hours tinkering. Coffee and food are fantastic. This is a favorite lunch place of mine.
Best breakfast sandwich in Chicago. Get the San Diego. Husband and wife team that work hard, make great food and run a tight ship
Best sandwiches in Chicago, nice atmosphere.
Cute mom and pop cafe to get work done. Friendly owner. Sometimes wifi doesn't work and you have to move your computer to a different area of the cafe to make it start working.

On a temperate Saturday in March, the guy working in Aje Cafe told my girlfriend that they were closing and she had to leave. She had 4 large bags with her, which I had left with her so I could run a quick errand up the block, so she asked if she could stay and hang out for another 5 minutes while he closed up while her boyfriend came back to help her with her bags.  The man working said, quote, "I'm F***ING TIRED of this S***, get out right now," quite aggressively, then said something about "working a hundred hours a week." When I returned to the cafe, she was sitting on the doorstep of the shop next door literally crying.  My girlfriend is a kind, quiet, introverted girl who likes to read and spend her time in libraries (she had been reading Nabokov in Aje Cafe) - think Belle from Beauty in the Beast, if she had to be a Disney princess - so I know she would not have asked for 5 minutes rudely or aggressively. And worse, the man inside was still behind the counter cleaning when I arrived, so she would not have prevented him from leaving the cafe by staying.  I've been to Aje Cafe many times, and the staff has always generally unpleasant and unhappy, especially if you tell them their WiFi password doesn't work (I was effectively told that I don't understand how to operate computers for 5 minutes, after which the barista realized the internet had cut out and she had to restart their router), but the food was always alright, so whatever, no big deal. But this was unacceptable.  There's a Peet's Coffee & Tea literally a block north on Clark Street, and everyone there is always VERY friendly and the atmosphere is just as cozy (and always cleaner) than at Aje Cafe. If you go just a few blocks further north to Belmont, then you'll find Kickstand Espresso Bar, which serves superior coffee and has a much friendlier vibe. Go to either of these places.  There is no reason to support Aje Cafe and its ungrateful, unfriendly staff. Go elsewhere.  And by the way: take their relatively high rating online with a grain of salt. Chicagoans, especially people living in Lakeview, love to pride themselves on "shopping local" and "supporting local business." Literally half of the 5-star reviews this place has gotten are completely based on the fact that they're a local cafe and not a large chain. Seriously. The fact that this place isn't Starbucks or Peet's automatically gets it a high rating from other people. But "local" doesn't mean "good" if everyone is a jerk.

I get breakfast here practically every Saturday morning. Their breakfast sandwiches are high quality and satisfying portions. They have potato cakes to pair too which is nice. I've also had a smoothie and you could really tell the ingredients were fresh where the flavors spoke for themselves without anything artificial going in.  They are a small mom and pop place. I've never seen more than 2 people working at a time. They can get busy and there can be a wait but it is well worth it.
My husband and I had a delicious sandwich and a wrap with sides of fresh fruit and pasta salad. Highly recommend! It's great for take-out or dine-in. We're going to try breakfast there tomorrow!
The food is unique healthy and delicious!

Awesome menu,cozy atmosphere, and spectacular service from the staff. We were a small group and at no time did anyone feel anything but appreciation from the people who were working. Oh, and they serve breakfast sammichs unit 2pm.

This is a great place for some good coffee and comfy seating. It is usually not that crowded and has good WiFi which makes it a good place for studying. Only problem is that the hours aren't the greatest
Very nice atmosphere. Very good coffee. Worker friendly.
The California club is the go to hangover cure after a long night of partying. The owners are super cool and the service is amazing. A small and cozy place to get work done if need to.

Love this place. I go about once a week because I work from home and like to get out and work somewhere other than my apartment when it gets too stuffy. The same two people work there all day/every day and they couldn't be nicer. Personally I think their coffee drinks are far better than any Starbucks, and the food is simply delicious. Awesome and quiet place to relax and do work. Great coffee and delicious sandwiches/soup. Get the pesto chicken and the italian wedding. If you can -- steal the couch by the window. Perfect place for people watching.
This place is very cute, and they have excellent mochas. The owner is nice and likes to check in to make sure you're happy with the food. Wifi is solid.

I love this cafe. It's perfect for working from home, job hunting, or just hanging out. It has outlets for your computers, which is a huge plus. The coffee is better than most chain coffee houses. I would definitely recommend this place and plan to come back soon!
Tasty breakfast sandwiches with good quality ingredients, a nice atmosphere, great Metropolis coffee, and not bad prices. Recommended.

I visited this establishment twice now. My first experience was sub-par. The cashier (a woman) wasn't personable and seemed to be annoyed when I asked for a sandwich suggestion. I brushed it off and thought perhaps she was having a bad day. The sandwich and salad I ordered were flavorful, albeit small portions for the price. Overall, I was unimpressed. I went back a second time for a coffee. The same woman was just as unpleasant as the first time I ordered. I asked for a small coffee in a medium cup, and she just stared at me. I reiterated my order. She looked at (who I presume to be) the owner, and shrugged. I looked at them both, confused by what I could have said to cause this. Anyway, I get the coffee - and it's basically hot water. I put in two packets of sugar for about 14 oz. of liquid - and all I can taste is sugar. I don't think I'll be back.
This place is a gem. I recommend the coffee drinks and the deluxe veggie sandwich, which I have about once a week, but you can't go wrong.
